# Hardware test — stage firmware on daas-dev

User flashes from **daas-dev** → NeoPC via `try_new_firmware.sh` (scp `fw_to_test/` + `/lib/firmware/rtl_bt/`).

## Agent: write flash artifacts here

After build + promote:

```
/root/rtl8761bu-libre/fw_to_test/rtl8761bu_fw.bin
/root/rtl8761bu-libre/fw_to_test/rtl8761bu_config.bin
```

Build in `rtl8761bu-libre/` (nested dir). Save profile siblings as `rtl8761bu_fw.<profile>.bin`.
Promote with `.cursor/skills/ub500-hardware-test/scripts/promote-test.sh <profile>`.

```bash
cd /root/rtl8761bu-libre/rtl8761bu-libre
docker build -t rtl8761bu-libre .
docker run --rm -v "$(pwd)":/work \
  -v /root/rtl8761bu-libre/rtl8761bu-non-free:/nf_ref:ro \
  -e NF_REF=/nf_ref/rtl8761bu_fw.bin \
  rtl8761bu-libre make <target>
```

## One test per handoff

Ship **one** profile per message. State clearly:

- **profile** name (`test-nf`, `minimal`, `full`, …)
- **expected SHA256** of `fw_to_test/rtl8761bu_fw.bin`
- user runs `try_new_firmware.sh` on NeoPC and pastes `journalctl` output

## Pass criteria

FC20: no `command 0xfc20 tx timeout`. Vendor baseline: `RTL: fw version 0x09a98a6b` + connect works.

On NeoPC PASS: `archive-hw-pass.sh <profile> <gate> "notes"` → `artifacts/hw-validated/`. Restore: `promote-test.sh --restore <sha>`. Start a **new chat** after a gate passes ([conversation-handoff.mdc](conversation-handoff.mdc)).
